issue.title: Non Fungible Token Spec
issue.body:
I came across this article https://hackernoon.com/an-overview-of-non-fungible-tokens-5f140c32a70a recently and I thought I would share it here in case it interests any of you.

Non Fungible Tokens are what is needed for individual seat ticketing like we were working on. The article defines Fungible as meaning something can be replaced by another identical item. Essentially meaning 20 bucks is 20 bucks and you don't care which exact bill you have.

They are working on establishing a standard interface for non fungible tokens called ERC-721. It will be interesting to follow it!

@christhomson @benjlcox @psycotica0-shopify

issue.title: Redirect on NewEvent doesn't fire using Metamask + Rinkeby
Redirect on NewEvent doesn't fire using Metamask + Rinkeby
Mist Issues
issue.body:
Mist has requirements about using callbacks, and things take longer on the real block chain.

This makes some more things async and has a little more "Loading" state.

issue.title: Arena Component Tech Debt
issue.body:
The Arena component is re-used from 2 fairly different contexts:
* on the NewEvent page its used to visualize what the arena will look like
* on the Event page we have actual tickets and need to mark if they are sold or not. We also have logic for selecting a seat. Each use case probably deserves its own component
